post_text:
A message from UNITED COMM SCHOOL DISTRICT

Dear United Families,
We are aware of the Governor’s announcement today that schools will remain closed for the remainder of the school year. This news does not change the plans we have in place today and for the next two weeks. Please continue with our continuous learning plan for the next couple of weeks and expect to get new information next week from your teachers and principal Rumor Clark about next steps. We recognize we need to address items such as technology, getting student items from their lockers and classrooms, and much more. Our team is working quickly so that we can communicate the next steps for United Community. We hope that you and your family are staying well during a difficult time.
text:
A message from UNITED COMM SCHOOL DISTRICT

Dear United Families,
We are aware of the Governor’s announcement today that schools will remain closed for the remainder of the school year. This news does not change the plans we have in place today and for the next two weeks. Please continue with our continuous learning plan for the next couple of weeks and expect to get new information next week from your teachers and principal Rumor Clark about next steps. We recognize we need to address items such as technology, getting student items from their lockers and classrooms, and much more. Our team is working quickly so that we can communicate the next steps for United Community. We hope that you and your family are staying well during a difficult time.

Drive-Through Breakfast and Lunch options (provided
by USDA) for kids in BOONE or surrounding area
Provided DAILY at the following locations and times:
Franklin Elementary , 1903 Crawford St., Boone, 12:00-12:30
Boone High School , Monona and 7th St. entrance, Boone, 11:00-11:30
Open Bible Church , 1224 Hancock Dr., Boone, 12:00-12:30

Meeker Elementary, 300 - 20th Street, Ames

Sawyer Elem., 4316 Ontario, Ames

post_text:
A message from UNITED COMM SCHOOL DISTRICT

Dear United Families,

As spring break comes to a close we are thinking about our students and what the next three weeks will bring. The principal will be conducting a virtual staff meeting with teachers next week to learn about the Department of Education recommendations related to this unexpected school closure. There will be further communication with families next week. Additionally we have applied for a waiver so that we too can add grab-&- go lunches to our school community. In the past United has never qualified for this USDA program so we have been working quickly to be able to follow the guidelines required to offer this program.

Our facilities are closed at this time so office phones are not being answered, but emails are being responded to daily. If you have a question, please email
Pam Dodge pdodge@united.k12.ia.us or Rumor Clark principal@united.k12.ia.us

(Updated at 3:51pm with corrected emails)

post_text:
A message from UNITED COMM SCHOOL DISTRICT

Governor Reynolds announced that she is recommending that Iowa school districts close for four weeks to mitigate the spread of COVID-19. The United Community will follow this direction. Effective Tuesday, March 17, all school buildings, events, practices, and activities are canceled until further notice.
Today will be our last day with childcare services as United’s Childcare will close tomorrow, March 18. We anticipate this program will also reopen on April 13. The secretary will contact families via email related to reimbursement information.
At this point we anticipate re-opening our school district on Monday, April 13. As we learn more or have additional information to communicate with families, we will do so.
Best regards.

post_text: United School Board member Kathy Toms received her "Better Boardsmanship" award at the recent Iowa School Board Association conference.This is her third consecutive year earning this award. It takes 125 credits each year with 85 being from formal learning. Toms was the only UC board member to earn the recognition this past year and one of under 60 in the state out of over1100 eligible school board members. Congratulations on your hard work!
